PN,31402
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1784911676
OL,3,CTerror in the Skies: The plot that
OL,4,Ccould have brought down the government
OL,6,FIn the upcoming ITV Exposure
OL,7,Fdocumentary, Terror in the Skies:
OL,8,FStopping the Liquid Bomb Plot, serving
OL,9,FMI5 officers speak publicly for the
OL,10,Ffirst time about the operation that
OL,11,Fbecame the biggest surveillance
OL,12,Foperation in British history.
OL,14,FAlongside ground-breaking AI
OL,15,Ftechnology to re-create pivotal
OL,16,Fscenes, senior counter-terrorism
OL,17,Fpolice, CIA analysts and government
OL,18,Fministers tell the inside story of a
OL,19,Frace to stop a conspiracy that
OL,20,Fthreatened thousands of lives.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/21
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31403
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1784911676
OL,3,CTerror in the Skies: The plot that
OL,4,Ccould have brought down the government
OL,6,FFor the first time, currently serving
OL,7,FMI5 officers describe the operation
OL,8,Ffrom the inside.
OL,10,FOne officer, given the pseudonym Dan,
OL,11,Frecalls secretly entering a suspected
OL,12,Fbomb-making flat in East London to
OL,13,Finstall surveillance equipment.
OL,15,F"When the door opened, and you're
OL,16,Flooking up into the darkness, and
OL,17,Fyou're not quite sure if there's
OL,18,Fanyone in," he said.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/21
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31404
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1784911676
OL,3,CTerror in the Skies: The plot that
OL,4,Ccould have brought down the government
OL,6,F"There is a degree of pressure... and
OL,7,Fobviously there's a potential
OL,8,Fconsequence of being hurt."
OL,10,FOperating in near-total darkness
OL,11,Fdemanded absolute precision.
OL,13,FHe said: "You're using almost no
OL,14,Flights. You're not giving the game
OL,15,Faway. If you open a door, if it's
OL,16,Fajar, you make sure when you come out
OL,17,Fyou put it exactly to the same
OL,18,Fposition it was in before."
OL,20,FAnd all of it had to be done without
OL,21,Falerting the suspects.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/21
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31405
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1784911676
OL,3,CTerror in the Skies: The plot that
OL,4,Ccould have brought down the government
OL,6,FAs Dan puts it: "Sometimes you're
OL,7,Fbreaking into someone's house, you're
OL,8,Fstanding in a terrorist's living room,
OL,9,Fand they have no idea."
OL,11,FAnother serving officer, who we're
OL,12,Fcalling Anna, describes the personal
OL,13,Fsacrifices required as the
OL,14,Finvestigation intensified.
OL,16,F"I dropped off the face of the earth
OL,17,Ffor a few weeks," she said. "Not long
OL,18,Fbefore I was due to get married."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/21
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31406
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1784911676
OL,3,CTerror in the Skies: The plot that
OL,4,Ccould have brought down the government
OL,6,FThe operation became so consuming that
OL,7,Fshe and her fiance eventually told
OL,8,Ftheir parents what she did for a
OL,9,Fliving "so that they didn't think I'd
OL,10,Fgone flaky".
OL,12,FLooking back, she reflects: "These are
OL,13,Fthe kind of jobs that we all join to
OL,14,Fwork on."
OL,16,FIn August 2006, investigators
OL,17,Funcovered what they believed was a
OL,18,Fplot orchestrated by British extremist
OL,19,FAbdulla Ahmed Ali and directed from
OL,20,FPakistan by the alleged mastermind
OL,21,FRashid Rauf.
OL,26,@oD@Rrr
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/21
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31407
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1784911676
OL,3,CTerror in the Skies: The plot that
OL,4,Ccould have brought down the government
OL,6,FThe conspiracy centred on smuggling
OL,7,Fliquid explosives involving plastic
OL,8,Fdrink bottles onto transatlantic
OL,9,Fpassenger aircraft departing from
OL,10,FHeathrow and bringing down multiple
OL,11,Fflights bound for North America.
OL,13,FAccording to those involved in the
OL,14,Finvestigation, the consequences could
OL,15,Fhave been catastrophic.
OL,17,FThe then MI5's deputy director
OL,18,Freflects that Britain "would not have
OL,19,Frecovered fully" and said the eventual
OL,20,Fdeath toll could have exceeded that of
OL,21,F9/11.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/21
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31408
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1784911676
OL,3,CTerror in the Skies: The plot that
OL,4,Ccould have brought down the government
OL,6,FMichael Chertoff, then US Homeland
OL,7,FSecurity Secretary, believes the
OL,8,Fimpact could have been so profound
OL,9,Fthat "you might not even have civil
OL,10,Faviation now".
OL,12,FThe operation became known as
OL,13,FOperation Overt.
OL,15,FLed by MI5 and Scotland Yard, it would
OL,16,Fgrow into what those involved describe
OL,17,Fas the biggest surveillance operation
OL,18,Fin British history.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/21
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31409
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1784911676
OL,3,CTerror in the Skies: The plot that
OL,4,Ccould have brought down the government
OL,6,FMore than 800 officers and staff were
OL,7,Fultimately engaged in monitoring
OL,8,Fsuspects, tracking movements,
OL,9,Fanalysing intelligence and building a
OL,10,Fpicture of a threat that was becoming
OL,11,Fmore alarming by the day.
OL,13,FAs surveillance intensified,
OL,14,Finvestigators gathered evidence they
OL,15,Fbelieved showed the conspirators were
OL,16,Fbuilding devices designed to evade
OL,17,Fairport security.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/21
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
